  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="page" n="4">
        <pb n="4"/>
        <lg>
          <l>בָּרְכוּ אֶת יְיָ הַמְבֹרָךְ!</l>
          <l>BAR’CHU et Adonai hamvorach!</l>
          <l>בָּרוּךְ יְיָ הַמְבֹרָךְ</l>
          <l>Baruch Adonai ham&apos;vorach</l>
          <l>לְעוֹלָם וָעֶד!</l>
          <l>l&apos;olam va-ed!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
          <l>PRAISE ADONAI to whom praise is due forever!</l>
          <l>Praised be Adonai to whom praise is due,</l>
          <l>now and forever!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
          <l>שְׁמַע וּבִרְכוֹתֶיהָ</l>
          <l>T</l>
          <l>SH&apos;MA UVIRCHOTEHA - SH&apos;MA AND ITS BLESSINGS</l>
        </lg>
        <lg>
          <l>All holy acts require summoning.</l>
          <l>For those who choose: The prayer leader at the word</l>
          <l>Bar&apos;chu (the call to worship) bends</l>
          <l>the knees and bows from the waist, and at &quot;Adonai stands straight. Baruch Adonai is the</l>
          <l>communal response, whereupon the community repeats the choreography of the first line.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
